{# End-of-simulation vote query.
   Election context (date, AC name, candidates) is passed in via
   `election_context` so the same template handles 2021 AE, 2024 LS, etc.

   Two anti-anchoring guard-rails (see distributional_analysis.md §H1, §H2):
     1. Explicit "reconsider your 2019 vote" frame — the persona's narrative
        was generated already-anchored to vote_2019_LS, so without this push
        the LLM tends to repeat the prior. We force a fresh decision.
     2. NOTA discouragement — empirically the model uses NOTA as an "I'm
        unsure" escape hatch. Real WB 2021 NOTA was 1.08% statewide; our
        first run got 5.67% (5× over-voted). Frame NOTA as active refusal
        only.
#}

